----------------- 2.- What's zMantis for?         ----------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------

 zMantis is designed to search projects in Mantis Bugtracking system and add
 desired emails (and their attachments) into Mantis Bugtracking system. 


-----------------------------------------------------------------
----------------- 3.- Compatibility              ----------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------
 zMantis has been tested in ZCS 6.x and Mantis Bugtracking system v5.5.x and above 
 It may or may not work properly with other versions.


-----------------------------------------------------------------
----------------- 4.- Installing zMantis          ----------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------
 Refer to INSTALL file for intructions of how to install this
 zimlet.


-----------------------------------------------------------------
----------------- 5.- Configuring zMantis         ----------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------
 There is no global configuration for zMantis, each user must 
 configure it separately.

 If zMantis has been correctly deployed, after loggin in zimbra, 
 a new icon should apperar in the left panel. Just click it and 
 a configuration window should appear with the following fields:

 Username: Mantis Bugtracking system username
 Password: Mantis Bugtracking system password
 Mantis Bugtracking system URL: Mantis Bugtracking system URL direction. It should use a secure 
	       connection, so be sure that 'https' is being used.
 LDAP Authentication: Enable this to send clean password otherwise
	       MD5 encryption will be used.
 Accounts: Enable this to retrieve account informations.
 Opportunities: Enable this to retrieve Opportunitie information.
 Projects: Enable this to retrieve Project information.
 Leads: Enable this to retrieve Leads information.
 
 Mark exported with tag: Set the tag name that will be used 
	to tag exported emails. If this field is empty, emails
	won't be tagged. This feature only works from the moment
	it is "activated", so previously exported emails won't 
	be tagged.
 
 After configuring zMantis, you can validate your connection to
 Mantis Bugtracking system by right-clicking the zMantis icon and choosing Force
 Authentication.

-----------------------------------------------------------------
----------------- 6.- Using zMantis               ----------------
-----------------------------------------------------------------
 There are three ways to access zMantis screen:

 - Using the Zimlet panel: 
   Just Drag a conversation or email and drop in the zMantis icon.

 - Using Toolbar Button:
   Select a conversation or email and click 'Send to Mantis Bugtracking system'
   toolbar button.

 - Using the context menu option:
   Rigth click a conversation or email and click 'Send to Mantis Bugtracking system' 
   option.

 After this, a new screen will appear with following sections:
 - Result Section:
    This section shows Mantis Bugtracking system response results. By default, 
    zMantis will search the FROM: contact of the email. It will show
    Accounts, Opportunities and Projects as configured (see 5.- 
    Configuring zMantis)

 - Contacts Dropbox
    We can request  Bugtracking system information of other contact in the selected
    email

 - Attachments list
    If email has any attachment, a list will appear. Checked attachments
    will be also imported into Mantis Bugtracking system 

